<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="cfcfea1b-6298-5494-9586-775320d249e6" activityNameId="7563bb96-54d1-417c-9ce4-33c4a0925f63" parentActivityId="89e7ddd3-f744-403a-b39d-d516befd3056" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">cleaning consumables, without water, in 13.6% solution state</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">cleaning product</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">cleaning agent</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts at the reception of materials and it includes water and energy for heating the water. </includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the production of 1 kg of cleaning product (100% active substance). This product should be used together with the appropriate input of water. Based on Golsteijn (2015), on average cleaning products contain 86% of water. The flow "water, completely softened, from decarbonised water at user" is recommended.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This activity aims at representing the production of an average kg (expressed as 100% active substance) of cleaning product. To do so, the life cycle inventory data of five product categories retrieved from Golsteijn et al (2015) have been averaged. The products are manual dishwashing detergents, window glass trigger spray cleaners, bathroom trigger spray cleaners, acid toilet cleaners and bleach toilet cleaners. The major active component in manual dishwashing detergents is a surfactant mix, which contributes to food residue removal. Other components of detergents may include solubility enhancers, preservatives, perfumes, dyes and opacifiers. On average cleaning products contain 86% of water. Based on the literature source Golsteijn (2015) the dataset used to represent the water flow is "water, completely softened, from decarbonised water at user". The values for heat, electricity, water and infrastructure are based on ecoinvent chemicals model. The model  is calculated based on literature data published by the industry. This value is a 5-year average of data (2011 - 2015) published by the Gendorf factory (Gendorf, 2016, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de), (Gendorf, 2015, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de),  (Gendorf, 2014, Umwelterklärung, www.gendorf.de).</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="68009ca2-60ee-4d5c-a36d-125adbe838a7">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2023:Manufacture of soap and detergents, cleaning and polishing preparations, pe</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The LCI study was developed by A.I.S.E., the International Association for Soaps, Detergents and Maintenance Products. The study refers to the European geography, it is here considered that it is valid as a GLO average.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The start date was sent to the year of publishing of the source of reference (Golsteijn et al, 2015). The data is considered to be still valid for the year of 2013.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2011-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The start date was sent to the year of publishing of the source of reference (Golsteijn et al, 2015). The data is considered to be still valid for the year of 2018.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
