        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated value. The global production volume is extrapolated from the European production volume using the global nominal GDP of 2010 (source: United Nations, http://data.un.org/Glossary.aspx?q=GDP+%28current+US%24%29, accessed 20180115). The annual production value of Europe in 2013 is 820.000.000 units (Golsteijn et al, 2015). This value is divided by the European share of global nominal GDP, 28.92%, considering the medium volume of 32.4 ml for each product unit and an average concentration of 13w/v%. </productionVolumeComment>
